    <statement><div><p>A small community in rural Kenya has an initial population of <m>{1050}</m> people. The population grows each year by a factor of <m>{\frac{53}{50}}</m>. Using indices, calculate the population after <m>{3}</m> years.</p>

<p>Write your answer using the model:</p>

<p><me>
P(t) = P_0 \times g^t
</me></p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>The population model is:</p>

<p><me>
P(t) = {1050} \times ({\frac{53}{50}})^{3}.
</me></p>

<p>Evaluating this gives:</p>

<p><me>
P(t) = {\frac{3126417}{2500}}.
</me></p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\frac{3126417}{2500}</m></p></answer>
